activities.text: What are the tax filing deadlines for Minnesota state income tax?

value.userQuery: What are the tax filing deadlines for Minnesota state income tax?

value.name: Answer
value.newValue:
Most people must file their 2023 Minnesota tax return by April 15, 2024. The Minnesota Department of Revenue must receive your return electronically – or have it delivered or postmarked – by that date. If you owe tax, you must pay by that date, even if you file your return later [1]​[2].

[1]: https://www.revenue.state.mn.us/income-tax-due-dates "Income Tax Due Dates | Minnesota Department of Revenue"
[2]: https://www.revenue.state.mn.us/press-release/2024-01-09/minnesota-individual-income-tax-filing-season-opens-january-29-2024 "Minnesota Individual Income Tax filing season opens January 29, 2024"

textCitations.text: The filing deadline to submit 2023 Minnesota income tax returns is Monday, April 15, 2024. This date matches the filing deadline for 2024 federal income tax returns. activities.text: Do I need to file a Minnesota state tax return if I only worked part-time or had a small amount of income?

value.userQuery: Do I need to file a Minnesota state tax return if I only worked part-time or had a small amount of income?

value.name: Answer
value.newValue:
You are required to file a Minnesota income tax return if your Minnesota gross income meets the minimum filing requirement, which is $13,825 for 2023. If your Minnesota gross income is less than the requirement, you should not be required to file a return [1].

[1]: https://www.revenue.state.mn.us/part-year-residents-income-tax-fact-sheet-2 "Part-Year Residents - Minnesota Department of Revenue"

2. **Second Retirement:** January 13, 1999 - After returning to the NBA and winning three more championships with the Bulls, Jordan retired again.
3. **Third Retirement:** April 16, 2003 - Jordan came out of retirement to play for the Washington Wizards and retired for the final time after the 2002-2003 season.
